(46, 15, 0, 'a:3:{i:1;s:5:"Array";i:2;s:5:"Array";i:3;s:5:"Array";}', 'a:3:{i:1;s:1298:&quot;&lt;div&gt;SharkImage copyrightGETTY IMAGES&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. Australia has a town called Humpty Doo.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more (ABC)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2. Every winter, great white sharks swim for 30 to 40 days to congregate at a particular spot halfway between Mexico and Hawaii. No-one knows why.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more (Slate)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. People touch their smartphones 2,617 times a day on average.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more (Network World)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4. Alcoholics in Ottawa are given wine every hour as part of their treatment.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;5. Three per cent of people think you should wait a month after the broadcast of a television programme before discussing the plot in a way that could throw up spoilers.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more (Vox)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;6. Even in the early 1970s women in the UK frequently had to get a male relative''s signature to get a loan.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;7. Pillows might easily have 47 different species of fungi living in them.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more (CNN)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;8. The Chilcot report is four-and-a-half times as long as War and Peace.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more (NBC)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;9. There was a Victorian comic song called &quot;Tony Blair&quot;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Find out more (Twitter)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;10. Fewer than one in five listed statues in the UK are of women.&lt;/div&gt;&quot;;i:2;s:15292:&quot;&lt;figure class=&quot;media-landscape no-caption full-width&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-stretch: inherit; font-family: Helmet, Freesans, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 24px; margin-right: -24.6406px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;span